original: Colliander, Knut Sven Gösta, komminister, Hyltebruk, f. 9/7/09 i Jönköp. av öv:löjtn. Gösta C. o. Mimi Just. G. 34 m. Hanna Österlind. Barn: Per f. 35, Kerstin 38, Eva 42. — Stud:’ex. i Örebro 27, teol. fil. ex. i Lund 29, teol. kand., prakt. teol. prov o. prästv. f. Växjö istift 32. Varit v. kommin. i Höigsby S’amt v. pastor i Fliseryd, va-kanskommin. i Färgaryd sed. 39. Ordf. i kyrkofullm.
translated: Colliander, Knut Sven Gösta, vicar, Hyltebruk, born on July 9, 1909 in Jönköping to Lieutenant Gösta C. and Mimi Just. Married in 1934 to Hanna Österlind. Children: Per born in 1935, Kerstin born in 1938, Eva born in 1942. Colliander attended high school in Örebro in 1927, received a degree in theology in Lund in 1929, became a candidate in theology, passed the practical theology exam and was ordained a priest in Växjö in 1932. He has been a vice vicar in Högsby, a pastor in Fliseryd, and a deputy vicar in Färgaryd since 1939. He was the chairman of the church council.
